-- China to End Prisoner Organ Donations in 5 Years, Xinhua Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2012-03-22T15:45:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-22/china-to-end-prisoner-organ-donations-in-5-years-xinhua-says.html
China  will abolish the practice of
transplanting organs from executed prisoners within five years,
as it builds a national organ-donation system, Xinhua News
Agency said, citing Vice Minister of Health Huang Jiefu.  China has set up trial transplant systems in 16 of the
nation’s 31 provincial-level regions, the official news service
said, citing Huang’s remarks to a conference in Hangzhou  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  